title: the_hurt_locker
body:
[i]"The rush of battle is a potent and often lethal addiction, for WAR IS A DRUG..."[/i] - Chris Hedges. [i]War is the Force That Gives Us Meanning[/i]. 2002.

[b]The Hurt Locker[/b] is a 2008 American war film about a three-man Explosive Ordnance Disposal ([[bomb]] disposal) team during the Iraq War. 

The film was directed by Kathryn Bigelow and the screenplay was written by Mark Boal, a freelance writer who was embedded as a journalist in 2004 with a U.S. Army EOD team in Iraq.

Because the film was not released in the United States until 2009, it was eligible for the 82nd Academy Awards, where it was nominated for nine Academy Awards. It won six Oscars, including Best Director for Bigelow (the first woman to win this award) and Best Picture. Boal won for Best Original Screenplay. 

The Hurt Locker earned numerous awards and honors from critics' organizations, festivals and groups, including six BAFTA Awards. However, it also received criticism by some in the [[military]] for various inaccuracies.

title: juuouki
body:
獣王記 ([i]Juuou-ki[/i], lit. [i]"Beast King's Chronicle"[/i]) is a 1988 beat'em up arcade [[video game]] developed and manufactured by [[Sega]]. Its North American title is [b]Altered Beast[/b].

The primary designer was "Uchida Makoto":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Makoto_Uchida , also responsible for the creation of the first [[Golden Axe]] game.

The game is set in Ancient Greece, and follows a beastman warrior [JP version] / centurion [EN version] who is unsealed/resurrected by Zeus to rescue his daughter Athena, and to do so becomes able to turn into beasts such as a magical [[werewolf]] with the use of power-ups to fight against legions of monsters and the undead. 

After its initial arcade release, it was ported to several home video game consoles and home computers, most notably the [[Sega Master System]] and the [[Sega Mega Drive]], for which it was a pack-in game. The Mega Drive version has been ported into the [[Nintendo 3DS]] as "”3D Juuouki”":http://archives.sega.jp/3d/juouki/ in 2013.

For its 2005 [[Playstation 2]] remake with a more [[science_fiction|sci-fi]] setting, use [[Juuouki ~PROJECT ALTERED BEAST~]] tag.

h4.Characters

There are some name differences between the Japanese and the English version

* [i]Juu-Senshi[/i] (Beastman Clan Warrior) [JP] / Resurrected [[centurion_(juuouki)|centurion]] [EN]

** Gold werewolf [JP] / [[Golden Werewolf]] [EN]

* [[athena (juuouki)|Athena]]

title: hinano_high_school_uniform
body:
The [[school uniform]] worn by students of the Hinano High School (陽菜野高校) in [i][[Action Heroine Cheer Fruits]][/i].

The uniform consists of:
* A [[grey shirt]] with a [[white sailor collar]].
** On summer, this is replaced by a [[white shirt]] with a [[blue sailor collar]].
* A [[neck ribbon]] with a color indicating the student's grade: [[Blue ribbon|Blue]] for first year, [[green ribbon|green]] for second year, and [[red ribbon|red]] for third year.
* A [[blue skirt]].
* Non-standardized legwear.
* [[Brown footwear|Brown]] of [[black footwear|black]] [[loafers]].

Additionally, [[Akagi An]] often wears [[black shorts|black]] [[bike shorts]] under her skirt.

title: heidern
body:
A character in [[SNK]]'s [[The King of Fighters]] series of games. He wears an eyepatch on his right eye after having lost it to [[Rugal Bernstein]] 8 years before [[The King of Fighters '94]]. Not wanting to be alone, he recruited [[Ralf Jones]] and [[Clark Still]] to form the [[Ikari (game)|Ikari Warriors]] 8 years later.

He has since adopted [[Leona Heidern|Leona]] since [[The King of Fighters '96]], after losing his biological daughter, Clara.

He fights using slashing attacks with his knife glove, a tradition of the Heidern family. He can create a cutting projectile with the glove as well as perform his Stormbringer, one of which he is famous for.

His signature catchphrase is "Go to Hell!" executed during the Final Bringer (since KOF 94) and Heidern's End (only from [[The King of Fighters '98|KOF 98]] through [[The King of Fighters 2001|2001]], he says "The End!" in [[The King of Fighters 2002|KOF 2002: Unlimited Match]] while executing said move).

title: paiwan
body:
Paiwan (Chinese: 排灣; pinyin: Páiwān) are an indigenous people of Taiwan. 

The majority of Paiwan people live in the southern chain of the Central Mountain Range, from Damumu Mountain and the upper Wuluo River in the north of the southern chain to the Hengchun Peninsula in the south of it, and also in the hills and coastal plains of southeastern Taiwan. There are two subgroups of the Paiwan people: the Raval and the Butsul
